fine. Fuck you.

475
00:34:48.186 --> 00:34:52.180
- Helen. open the window.
- No. there's too much smoke.

476
00:34:52.457 --> 00:34:54.551
- We have to get out of here.
- What?

477
00:34:54.626 --> 00:34:56.026
Open up. Come on. get out.

478
00:34:57.996 --> 00:34:59.396
What the fuck. Noah?

479
00:34:59.464 --> 00:35:01.175
The fire's coming. We
have to get out of here.

480
00:35:01.199 --> 00:35:02.997
No. They just told us to stay.

481
00:35:03.068 --> 00:35:06.232
- Who did?
- Some... this... guy.

482
00:35:06.605 --> 00:35:08.516
He said the traffic's starting
to move down at the bottom.

483
00:35:08.540 --> 00:35:11.942
- we just have to wait a few minutes.
- It's not true. The fire is an hour away.

484
00:35:12.010 --> 00:35:13.376
We have to get out of here.

485
00:35:13.445 --> 00:35:15.414
Don't worry. look. You
see this ridge right here?

486
00:35:15.480 --> 00:35:17.449
I've hiked it before.
There's a fire road up here.

487
00:35:17.515 --> 00:35:18.448
it goes down to the ocean.

488
00:35:18.516 --> 00:35:20.747
- We just have to get up there.
- Okay. what about them?

489
00:35:23.822 --> 00:35:24.687
Who the fuck are they?

490
00:35:24.756 --> 00:35:27.168
- I don't know. I picked them up.
- They don't have a car.

491
00:35:27.192 --> 00:35:28.336
They'll have to come with us.

492
00:35:28.360 --> 00:35:30.522
- She's pregnant.
- Oh. fuck. look. Helen.

493
00:35:30.595 --> 00:35:32.039
I don't know what to
say. but we have to go.

494
00:35:32.063 --> 00:35:35.295
Movement is life. If we stay
here. we'll probably fucking die.

495
00:35:37.869 --> 00:35:38.869
Fuck.

496
00:35:40.038 --> 00:35:42.064
Forget the car. we got to go.

497
00:35:47.078 --> 00:35:48.078
Ah. fuck.

498
00:35:52.884 --> 00:35:55.353
- They coming?
- No. Now. what?

499
00:35:56.054 --> 00:35:57.054
Here.

500
00:35:57.856 --> 00:36:00.189
Take this. Follow me.

501
00:36:13.138 --> 00:36:16.040
Okay. we need to get
down there. cross the ravine.

502
00:36:16.107 --> 00:36:17.518
- and hike up the other side.
- That's miles.

503
00:36:17.542 --> 00:36:18.902
It's not. it's okay.
We can do it.

504
00:36:20.478 --> 00:36:22.106
- No. No way.
- Helen...

505
00:36:23.815 --> 00:36:25.909
I know you're scared.
but you got to trust me.

506
00:36:34.793 --> 00:36:35.817
Shit.

507
00:36:44.703 --> 00:36:45.703
All right?

508
00:37:43.862 --> 00:37:47.026
- Is this how we're gonna die?
- Probably not.

509
00:37:50.535 --> 00:37:52.663
Jesus. I don't want to die.

510
00:37:53.071 --> 00:37:55.006
Neither do I. so
let's just keep going.

511
00:37:59.511 --> 00:38:01.810
You seemed pretty
resigned to it three hours ago.

512
00:38:02.680 --> 00:38:03.909
Yeah. I guess I was.

513
00:38:05.283 --> 00:38:06.283
And?

514
00:38:08.553 --> 00:38:09.553
Why? You disappointed?

515
00:38:12.090 --> 00:38:13.353
What happened?

516
00:38:14.559 --> 00:38:16.994
- Ah. you'll think I'm nuts.
- Try me.

517
00:38:17.695 --> 00:38:18.993
I listened to the recordings

518
00:38:19.063 --> 00:38:21.726
of the depositions that
Alison and I gave to Jeffries.

519
00:38:23.301 --> 00:38:24.301
Yeah?

520
00:38:25.804 --> 00:38:27.102
I don't know. it was just...

521
00:38:27.405 --> 00:38:29.840
It was just hearing my own
voice from back then and...

522
00:38:30.275 --> 00:38:32.540
it reminded me of
something I used to know.

523
00:38:33.111 --> 00:38:34.111
What?

524
00:38:37.081 --> 00:38:38.140
How to be happy.

525
00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:45.346
Eh. you think I'm crazy.

526
00:38:56.768 --> 00:38:58.566
I keep thinking about
what Whitney said.

527
00:38:58.636 --> 00:39:02.471
that her worst fear is
really turning into me.

528
00:39:03.241 --> 00:39:06.370
- She was upset. She didn't mean it.
- No. she absolutely meant it.

529
00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:09.007
Said I was codependent.

530
00:39:09.948 --> 00:39:12.713
If Whitney turns
out anything like you.

531
00:39:13.284 --> 00:39:16.118
she should count
herself fucking lucky.

532
00:39:17.522 --> 00:39:20.651
I don't know. maybe she's
right. Maybe I am a pathetic.

533
00:39:20.725 --> 00:39:22.819
desperate enabler.

534
00:39:22.894 --> 00:39:24.829
I've never been able to
stand on my own two feet.

535
00:39:26.898 --> 00:39:27.898
You're not.

536
00:39:32.270 --> 00:39:34.739
Well. thank you. but I'm not
sure I can trust your opinion.

537
00:39:35.240 --> 00:39:37.038
Well. what about what
she said about me?

538
00:39:37.775 --> 00:39:38.775
What'd she say?

539
00:39:39.677 --> 00:39:41.703
That I burn through
people. that I...

540
00:39:43.181 --> 00:39:44.706
use them up and discard them.

541
00:39:44.782 --> 00:39:46.182
Think she's right about that?

542
00:39:47.352 --> 00:39:48.352
You want the truth?

543
00:39:50.355 --> 00:39:51.355
Yeah. I know.

544
00:39:52.156 --> 00:39:53.556
- You do?
- Yeah. of course I do.

545
00:39:53.625 --> 00:39:55.093
Well. why do you do it?

546
00:39:56.995 --> 00:39:57.995
Wish I knew.

547
00:39:59.264 --> 00:40:01.961
I always thought it was because
you were so deeply insecure.

548
00:40:02.033 --> 00:40:04.229
you were afraid if you stayed
with someone long enough.

549
00:40:04.302 --> 00:40:06.066
they'd find out how
inadequate you are.

550
00:40:06.671 --> 00:40:07.671
Thanks.

551
00:40:08.306 --> 00:40:11.572
I know it sounds harsh. but we're
basically flirting with death here. right?

552
00:40:11.643 --> 00:40:12.542
Oh. fuck.

553
00:40:12.610 --> 00:40:13.888
I mean. I might not
get another chance to...

554
00:40:13.912 --> 00:40:14.936
Helen. wait.

555
00:40:19.384 --> 00:40:20.613
Oh. shit.

556
00:40:29.661 --> 00:40:31.789
- I guess we climb down.
- Oh. my God.

557
00:40:34.499 --> 00:40:36.365
We can't hike back.
That's not an option.

558
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:37.993
Yeah. but I can't
climb down that.

559
00:40:38.069 --> 00:40:40.470
- I mean. I can't.
- It's not that far.

560
00:40:45.643 --> 00:40:46.643
Oh. God.

561
00:40:52.984 --> 00:40:55.385
Okay. Okay. look.

562
00:40:55.787 --> 00:40:56.811
How about I go first

563
00:40:57.155 --> 00:40:58.714
- and find a way down?
- No.

564
00:40:58.790 --> 00:41:00.734
And then. if I fall. at least
the kids will have you.

565
00:41:00.758 --> 00:41:02.090
- Oh. my God. no! Wait.
- No. no.

566
00:41:02.160 --> 00:41:03.671
- What? We'll just wait!
- But if I make it. I'll make it.

567
00:41:03.695 --> 00:41:06.130
I'll make it. okay?
And I'll guide you down.

568
00:41:06.197 --> 00:41:07.825
And then if you
fall. I'll catch you.

569
00:41:07.899 --> 00:41:10.801
- I'll crush you. That's insane.
- You're okay.

570
00:41:10.868 --> 00:41:13.647
I mean. it's idiotic. It's just... There's
got to be another way out of here

571
00:41:13.671 --> 00:41:15.333
if we just hike back to...

572
00:41:15.406 --> 00:41:16.533
Oh. my God. Noah!

573
00:41:16.607 --> 00:41:18.200
Shit. Just follow me.

574
00:41:18.276 --> 00:41:20.711
Noah! Noah!

575
00:42:14.932 --> 00:42:16.127
Noah!

576
00:42:16.534 --> 00:42:18.332
I'm okay. I'm okay.

577
00:42:37.221 --> 00:42:38.484
Okay. your turn.

578
00:42:41.292 --> 00:42:42.292
Helen?

579
00:42:45.163 --> 00:42:47.064
Come on. you can do this.

580
00:42:47.565 --> 00:42:48.931
No. I'm good.

581
00:42:49.467 --> 00:42:52.904
You should just go get help
and come back and get me.

582
00:42:54.338 --> 00:42:57.467
Helen. you can't just sit
there. That's not an option.

583
00:42:57.909 --> 00:42:59.104
I think it is.

584
00:42:59.710 --> 00:43:01.178
You have to trust me.

585
00:43:01.245 --> 00:43:03.077
Why would I trust you?

586
00:43:03.147 --> 00:43:06.675
Every time I trust you.
something terrible happens.

587
00:43:13.925 --> 00:43:15.188
Helen. please.

588
00:43:16.527 --> 00:43:18.428
The kids... The kids need you.

589
00:43:20.031 --> 00:43:21.260
I need you.

590
00:43:22.900 --> 00:43:24.630
We can't do this without you.

591
00:43:26.571 --> 00:43:27.800
Please come down.

592
00:43:32.110 --> 00:43:33.237
Oh. fuck.

593
00:43:38.483 --> 00:43:40.281
Okay. that's
great! That's great.

594
00:43:41.853 --> 00:43:43.845
You got it.

595
00:43:52.563 --> 00:43:53.963
Go on. that's it.

596
00:43:54.232 --> 00:43:55.256
You got it.

597
00:44:10.648 --> 00:44:12.549
That's it. You
got it. you got it.

598
00:44:13.451 --> 00:44:15.579
Okay. there's a hold
just a few inches down.

599
00:44:15.653 --> 00:44:17.144
Test it first!

600
00:44:17.889 --> 00:44:19.448
- Oh. my God.
- Ah. fuck!

601
00:44:19.524 --> 00:44:20.890
Oh. are you okay?

602
00:44:23.861 --> 00:44:24.885
Yeah. I'm fine.

603
00:44:27.365 --> 00:44:29.231
- I'm stuck.
- No. you're not.

604
00:44:29.734 --> 00:44:32.761
There's a foothold just
below the one you just tested.

605
00:44:41.546 --> 00:44:43.515
I can't reach it.

606
00:44:43.581 --> 00:44:46.326
Yes. you can. but you have to let go
of your right hand and bend your knee.

607
00:44:46.350 --> 00:44:47.443
Where's this foot?

608
00:44:48.019 --> 00:44:49.078
Shit. okay.

609
00:44:54.625 --> 00:44:55.625
That's it.

610
00:44:55.860 --> 00:44:58.853
It's like two inches below
where you want it to be.

611
00:45:01.866 --> 00:45:04.563
Helen. you can't just freeze.
You have to keep going.

612
00:45:04.802 --> 00:45:06.168
Movement is life.

613
00:45:06.637 --> 00:45:07.637
You know what?

614
00:45:07.705 --> 00:45:10.368
Could you please fucking stop
mansplaining to me right now?

615
00:45:10.808 --> 00:45:12.902
I'm not mansplaining. I'm...

616
00:45:13.644 --> 00:45:15.756
Look. you're hanging
from a fucking rock face

617
00:45:15.780 --> 00:45:16.780
and you might die.

618
00:45:16.814 --> 00:45:18.009
I-I'm just trying to help.

619
00:45:18.082 --> 00:45:19.826
I am not gonna fucking
die. and the only reason

620
00:45:19.850 --> 00:45:22.319
I'm hanging from a rock
face is because of you.

621
00:45:22.386 --> 00:45:23.911
Because you don't plan.

622
00:45:24.288 --> 00:45:25.483
You don't think ahead.

623
00:45:25.556 --> 00:45:29.186
You just do what you want and you
don't think about the consequences.

624
00:45:29.627 --> 00:45:32.256
- I don't think that's fair.
- And another thing.

625
00:45:33.264 --> 00:45:36.757
What the fuck is up with this
"movement is life" bullshit?

626
00:45:36.834 --> 00:45:38.826
That is just something
that men say.

627
00:45:39.237 --> 00:45:40.237
Oh.

628
00:45:41.239 --> 00:45:42.935
"I couldn't stay with my wife.

629
00:45:43.007 --> 00:45:45.636
I had to leave my
family because..."

630
00:45:45.710 --> 00:45:47.679
"movement is life."

631
00:45:47.845 --> 00:45:50.872
It's such self-serving hogwash.

632
00:45:56.654 --> 00:45:59.055
Ooh! Oh. my gosh.

633
00:45:59.357 --> 00:46:01.155
Ooh.

634
00:46:01.225 --> 00:46:03.057
Nice work.

635
00:46:03.127 --> 00:46:04.789
You can hit me if you want to.

636
00:46:14.138 --> 00:46:15.138
Helen.

637
00:46:17.441 --> 00:46:18.465
Look.

638
00:46:18.943 --> 00:46:21.003
Oh. my God.

639
00:46:21.078 --> 00:46:22.078
We did it.

640
00:46:23.180 --> 00:46:24.409
Come on. Let's go.

641
00:46:28.452 --> 00:46:30.318
- Is that the ravine?
- Yeah.

642
00:46:31.122 --> 00:46:33.091
Now we just have to
go all the way back up.

643
00:46:37.762 --> 00:46:39.573
So we were gonna have
a buffet 'cause it's cheaper.

644
00:46:39.597 --> 00:46:41.275
but it's gonna be impossible
to keep the food warm

645
00:46:41.299 --> 00:46:43.791
- in those weather conditions.
- Isn't the tent heated?

646
00:46:44.168 --> 00:46:46.313
Yeah. but it's probably
gonna be below freezing.

647
00:46:46.337 --> 00:46:48.499
so I think maybe we
should just get 'em to plate it

648
00:46:48.572 --> 00:46:51.701
and then cancel the steak.

649
00:46:52.276 --> 00:46:54.211
Half their friends
are vegan anyway.

650
00:46:57.715 --> 00:46:59.026
I can't believe
you did all that.

651
00:46:59.050 --> 00:47:01.050
- What?
- You planned the whole wedding.

652
00:47:01.886 --> 00:47:03.081
You want to know a secret?

653
00:47:03.154 --> 00:47:05.487
I really enjoyed it.

654
00:47:09.060 --> 00:47:10.404
I'll talk to her. I'll get
her to change her mind.

655
00:47:10.428 --> 00:47:12.226
No. no. don't. don't.

656
00:47:12.697 --> 00:47:14.608
Don't. It's what she
wants. and I don't want to...

657
00:47:14.632 --> 00:47:16.464
Just... just let it be.

658
00:47:22.340 --> 00:47:24.571
Can I ask you something
I don't understand?

659
00:47:25.142 --> 00:47:26.142
Of course.

660
00:47:27.645 --> 00:47:30.376
I don't understand how you can
be so compassionate sometimes

661
00:47:30.448 --> 00:47:33.213
and sometimes so cruel.

662
00:47:35.886 --> 00:47:38.355
I mean. we all have our
darkness and our bad qualities.

663
00:47:38.422 --> 00:47:40.288
but with you. the...

664
00:47:42.293 --> 00:47:44.125
Dichotomy is extreme?

665
00:47:45.730 --> 00:47:46.730
Yes.

666
00:47:49.166 --> 00:47:51.260
Yeah. I've asked myself
the same question.

667
00:47:53.170 --> 00:47:55.196
I don't know. I thought
about my childhood.

668
00:47:56.607 --> 00:47:58.940
My mother was always dying
and my father was never there.

669
00:47:59.009 --> 00:48:00.671
and when he was.
he was so angry...

670
00:48:02.313 --> 00:48:04.305
I just wanted to be
somewhere else.

671
00:48:04.715 --> 00:48:06.513
Someone else. And then...

672
00:48:08.352 --> 00:48:10.651
And then. I got to college
and I met you. and...

673
00:48:10.721 --> 00:48:12.553
and you looked at
me with fresh eyes

674
00:48:12.623 --> 00:48:16.253
and you told me how
much potential I had. and...

675
00:48:16.394 --> 00:48:18.124
that I was gonna
be this great artist.

676
00:48:18.496 --> 00:48:21.295
I remember thinking to
myself. I actually said to myself.

677
00:48:21.699 --> 00:48:22.860
"Don't get caught.

678
00:48:23.467 --> 00:48:25.800
Don't let her see the
cracks. and you'll be okay."

679
00:48:27.037 --> 00:48:28.835
- Really?
- Yeah. Really.

680
00:48:29.407 --> 00:48:30.875
And I'm sorry. I...

681
00:48:30.941 --> 00:48:34.537
That's no way to begin a
relationship. but I know that now.

682
00:48:35.946 --> 00:48:37.676
You can't lie your way
through a marriage.

683
00:48:37.748 --> 00:48:40.588
hiding from the one person who
knows you better than anyone else. and...

684
00:48:41.185 --> 00:48:43.086
resenting her when
she starts to figure it out.

685
00:48:43.154 --> 00:48:45.419
And then hating her
for loving you anyway.

686
00:48:46.824 --> 00:48:48.368
Because what kind
of an idiot must she be

687
00:48:48.392 --> 00:48:50.520
if she can't see what
a loser you really are?

688
00:48:53.798 --> 00:48:57.758
That's what I did to you. and
I put my self-hatred onto you.

689
00:49:01.238 --> 00:49:02.831
And I'm really fucking sorry.

690
00:49:11.549 --> 00:49:13.108
I was lying. too.

691
00:49:13.317 --> 00:49:15.028
No. you weren't. You're the
most honest person I know.

692
00:49:15.052 --> 00:49:16.520
No. I was.

693
00:49:17.755 --> 00:49:22.193
I mean. I tried to make
you think I was this cool girl.

694
00:49:22.259 --> 00:49:24.160
this cool. easygoing person.

695
00:49:24.395 --> 00:49:27.331
- You were never easygoing.
- Well...

696
00:49:27.398 --> 00:49:30.766
You know. you know what I mean.

697
00:49:30.835 --> 00:49:31.859
Independent.

698
00:49:31.936 --> 00:49:35.270
You know. autonomous.

699
00:49:35.940 --> 00:49:37.909
- You sure had me convinced.
- I know I did.

700
00:49:39.109 --> 00:49:41.010
But I wasn't...

701
00:49:41.979 --> 00:49:45.916
I really wasn't even a person then. I
was like a performance of a person.

702
00:49:46.484 --> 00:49:47.975
And all I really wanted

703
00:49:48.586 --> 00:49:53.547
was someone to save me
from Bruce and Margaret.

704
00:49:55.593 --> 00:50:00.395
And then what I did
to you was so unfair

705
00:50:00.464 --> 00:50:03.798
because I brought
you into my family

706
00:50:03.868 --> 00:50:06.133
with the promise of
all of this opportunity.

707
00:50:06.203 --> 00:50:08.263
and I knew my dad would
be threatened by you.

708
00:50:08.339 --> 00:50:10.467
And then I just set you
up to be the obstacle.

709
00:50:10.541 --> 00:50:14.501
like. to just take the
heat. fight the fights.

710
00:50:15.646 --> 00:50:18.639
I mean. I never stood up for you
against them. I said I did. but I didn't.

711
00:50:22.019 --> 00:50:23.019
No. you didn't.

712
00:50:25.489 --> 00:50:27.014
So I'm sorry. too.

713
00:50:35.499 --> 00:50:36.592
Well. okay.

714
00:50:42.206 --> 00:50:44.835
- Can I ask you another question?
- Anything.

715
00:50:45.576 --> 00:50:47.772
If you had never met Alison.

716
00:50:49.113 --> 00:50:51.480
if we had stayed in the city

717
00:50:51.549 --> 00:50:53.960
and not gone to my parents' house
that summer like you wanted to.

718
00:50:53.984 --> 00:50:55.919
do you think we
would still be together?

719
00:50:57.888 --> 00:50:59.789
I mean. would I ever
have been enough for you?

720
00:51:02.927 --> 00:51:04.259
Which answer do you want?

721
00:51:05.429 --> 00:51:06.429
The truth.

722
00:51:09.567 --> 00:51:11.763
It was me who wasn't
enough. It wasn't you. I mean...

723
00:51:12.836 --> 00:51:16.068
I said to Jeffries I had no idea
why it happened. but that's not true.

724
00:51:16.874 --> 00:51:20.140
I just felt so bad
about myself back then.

725
00:51:21.679 --> 00:51:23.580
